5. **Anthropic "brake pedal"** — Jack Clark's pause call lands 3 weeks before S-1; METR task-length doubling every 4 months
6. **NotebookLM + Gemini 3.5** — secure cloud computer is the same runtime as Gemini Managed Agents
7. **Meta Hatch at $200/mo** — running on Claude Sonnet during test phase, transition to Muse Spark planned

**Day's real story** (in `insight_analysis`): Three layers converged — compute consolidated into three contracts, models went public, and the application layer bifurcated into on-device (Apple), cheap-inference (Xiaomi), and consumer-bundled (Meta). Anthropic's pause call and the OpenAI IPO are happening on the same week because, post-IPO, the gas pedal and the brake pedal become the same pedal.

